	<title>Trigonometry</title>
    
    <p>A trigonometría pódese realizar usando as <link xref="function">funcións</link> sen, cos e tan.</p>
    <example>
    <p>sen 45</p>
    </example>
    <p>
    The angle units used can be changed from the <guiseq><gui>Calculator</gui><gui>Preferences</gui></guiseq> menu.
    Trigonometry buttons are visible when in <link xref="mouse">Advanced mode</link>.
    </p>
    <p>As funcións hiperbólicas están dispoñíbeis engadindo unha «h» ao final da función.</p>
    <example>
    <p>sinh 0.34</p>
    </example>
    <p>
    Inverse functions are entered either using the inverse symbol ⁻¹ (<keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>I</key></keyseq>) or the "a" form of the function.
    The following two equations are equivalent.
    </p>
    <example>
    <p>sin⁻¹ 0.5</p>
    <p>asin 0.5</p>
    </example>   
    <p>
    To enter <link xref="variable">π</link> with the keyboard use <keyseq><key>Ctrl</key><key>P</key></keyseq>.
    </p>
